text: Hendry County is a county in the U.S. state of Florida, and was formed on February 4, 1832. As of 2020, 39,619 people lived there. Hendry County's seat is La Belle. ==References== ==Other websites== *Official county website Category:Florida counties Category:1923 establishments in the United States Category:1920s establishments in Florida
